14
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:37,690
Last Saturday, the UN Security Council

15
00:00:37,690 --> 00:00:40,530
unanimously voted for tough new sanctions

16
00:00:40,530 --> 00:00:41,850
against North Korea.

17
00:00:41,850 --> 00:00:44,039
It’s part of ongoing efforts to stop

18
00:00:44,039 --> 00:00:46,850
North Korea from making nuclear weapons.

19
00:00:46,850 --> 00:00:48,500
Not only is this newsworthy.

20
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,370
It’s Twitter worthy.

21
00:00:50,370 --> 00:00:52,500
Yes, China and Russia voted with us

22
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,089
on these sanctions.

23
00:00:54,089 --> 00:00:57,220
And they cover more than $1 billion dollars
in exports—

24
00:00:57,220 --> 00:01:00,359
including coal, iron, lead, and seafood.

25
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:03,450
Meaning North Korea can’t sell those things
abroad.

26
00:01:03,450 --> 00:01:05,880
Of course, that just means all that seafood

27
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,860
